  • Constructor Details

    • SpectralWCS

      public SpectralWCS()
      Creates a new SpectralWCS

    • SpectralWCS

      public SpectralWCS(CoordAxis1D axis, String specsys, String ssysobs, String ssyssrc, Double restfrq, Double restwav, Double velosys, Double zsource, Double velang, String bandpassName, EnergyTransition transition, Double resolvingPower)
      full parameter constructor.
      Parameters:
      axis - description of the one-dimensional energy axis.
      specsys - reference frame for the spectral coordinate.
      ssysobs - reference frame that is constant over the range of the non-spectral world coordinates.
      ssyssrc - reference frame for the velocity of the source (zsource).
      restfrq - rest frequency of the spectral feature of interest.
      restwav - rest wavelength of the spectral feature of interest.
      velosys - correction for the observatory's motion with respect to the barycenter.
      zsource - redshift of the source (relative to ssyssrc).
      velang - angle of true velocity from tangent to line of sight.
      bandpassName - telescope- or instrument-specific name for the energy band covered by the data; this is usually a filter name.
      transition - description of the energy transition observed.
      resolvingPower - ratio of wavelength to resolution (lambda/delta-lambda).
